Results current as of Mon, 10 Mar 2025

Another rough week brought in some new faces to the top tier! Welcome to Boluo, usersandra, Dhanush Binu, z6fan. Markets remain volatile as we enter into a new regime, and the competition is still anyone’s game to win. Special congratulations go out to 161803 (who we’ll call ‘Phil’) for posting a massive GMRR of 0.8% per trading day. Phil earned this return by betting against the SP500 with a beta of -1.05, which so far has been a winning bet. Let’s see if he can keep it up!

It’s impressive how many traders have managed to hedge out volatility and remain posting positive returns with good Sharpes. Congrats to all!

Current Rankings

gmrr, vol, and sharpe are calculated on a per-trading day basis using end-of-day Net Asset Values of each trader’s account. See the scoring section for an in-depth explaination.

  • rank: overall ranking in the competition. Your tier appears as the whole number and your ranking within your tier appears as a decimal; for example, Trader 3.4 is ranked #4 in the 3rd tier.

  • gmrr: Geometric mean of rate of return

  • vol: Volatility of returns

  • sharpe: (gmrr - rf) / vol
